h5. Problem description
createdvsresolved JIRA Portlet gadget is rendered in a funky way. In Firefox, the gadget will be rendered in half. Same problem in IE7, clicking on the gear button will expand the gadget albeit that the {{refresh}} menu cannot be minimized.

h5. Steps to replicate:
# Add the createdvsresolved gadget into Confluence:
{code}
http://jira.atlassian.com/rest/gadgets/1.0/g/com.atlassian.jira.gadgets:created-vs-resolved-issues-chart-gadget/gadgets/createdvsresolved-gadget.xml
{code}
# In a page, use this wiki markup:
{code}
{gadget:url=http://jira.atlassian.com/rest/gadgets/1.0/g/com.atlassian.jira.gadgets:created-vs-resolved-issues-chart-gadget/gadgets/createdvsresolved-gadget.xml|border=false}projectOrFilterId=filter-19761&periodName=daily&daysprevious=30&isCumulative=true&showUnresolvedTrend=false&versionLabel=major&isConfigured=true&refresh=false{gadget}
{code}

In Firefox 3.6.8 the gadget will be displayed like this:
[^sc1.jpg]

In IE7, it will also be displayed like the above picture, but clicking on the gear button will expand the chart - but you can see a broken menu on the right hand side bottom corner:
[^sc2.jpg]

